               <head>Miscellaneous works on Sufism and literature, 6 items (a-f)</head>
               <msContents class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2006003807 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85129660">
                  <summary>Miscellaneous collection of works on Sufism and literary commentary, comprised of fragments extracted from several heterogeneous sources. 
Volume not dated. 
Rough nastaʿlīq, shikastah āmīz, and taʿlīq scripts by multiple hands. Limited annotations in margins. 
Intermittent foliation in pencil. 
Lacking original binding.
Plain paper dust wrapper. 
Folios mostly unbound; water and fungal stains, cropped, wormholes, later paper repairs. 
Condition fragile. 
</summary>
                  <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic </textLang>
                  <msItem n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1406B-item1">
                     <locus from="1r" to="2v">ff. 1r-2v </locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic </textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Delhi Persian 1406B a. 
</p>
                        <p>Fragment of an untitled list of Arabic and Persian works and volumes by an unnamed compiler.
</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end; datable to the early nineteenth century. 
</p>
                        <p>Flyleaf 1Av comprises a fragment extracted from an Arabic religious text. 
</p>
                     </note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="2" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1406B-item2">
                     <locus from="3r" to="111v">ff. 3r-111v </locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Delhi Persian 1406B b. 
</p>
                        <p>Fragment of an untitled commentary by an unnamed author explaining the lyrics or ghazalīyāt of <persName key="viaf_56731778" role="ant">Shams al-Dīn Muḥammad Shīrāzī takhalluṣ Ḥāfiẓ</persName> (d. 792/1390). 
                        </p>
                        <p>The present copy is defective at the beginning and end. 
</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end; datable to the eighteenth century. 
</p>
                        <p>Annotations in margins. 
</p>
                        <p>Quotations in red. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic </textLang>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="3" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1406B-item3">
                     <locus from="112r" to="154r">ff. 112r-154r </locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Delhi Persian 1406B c. 
</p>
                        <p>Fragment of an untitled Sufi treatise on correct moral conduct by an unnamed author. 
</p>
                        <p>The present copy starts into bāb or chapter six and extends until bāb twenty-six. 
</p>
                        <p>The present copy is defective at the beginning and end. 
</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end; datable to the eighteenth century. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic  </textLang>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="4" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1406B-item4">
                     <locus from="155r" to="158v">ff. 155r-158v </locus>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_22139">رسالهٴ حليه</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Delhi Persian 1406B d. 
</p>
                        <p>Hagiographic treatise by an unnamed author in praise of the Prophet Muḥammad, based on extracts from the <title key="work_22139">Madārij al-nubuvvah</title> by the celebrated muḥaddis̲ of Delhi, <persName key="viaf_45690112" role="ant">ʿAbd al-Ḥaqq ibn Sayf al-Dīn</persName>. 
                        </p>
                        <p>The present copy is defective at the end. 
</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end; datable to the early nineteenth century. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic </textLang>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="5" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1406B-item5">
                     <locus from="159r" to="160v">ff. 159r-160v </locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Delhi Persian 1406B e. 
</p>
                        <p>Fragment of an untitled commentary on the poems of the celebrated poet and Sufi, Mawlānā <persName key="viaf_98930150" role="ant">Rūmī Balkhī</persName> (d. 672/1273), by an unnamed author. 
                        </p>
                        <p>The present copy is defective at the beginning and end. 
</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end; datable to the late eighteenth century. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic </textLang>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="6" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1406B-item6">
                     <locus to="161v" from="161r">f. 161</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Delhi Persian 1406B f. 
</p>
                        <p>Fragment of an untitled Arabic treatise on medicine by an unnamed author. 
</p>
                        <p>The work describes <persName key="viaf_89770781" role="ant">Ibn Sīnā</persName> as an authority. 
                        </p>
                        <p>Although the present copy is defective at the beginning, the text ends abruptly without formal conclusion or colophon. 
</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end; datable to the early nineteenth century. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="ar">Arabic </textLang>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
